serpentine armlets~
These armlets are actually a pair of ebony and ivory anacondas dancing in
circles around one another, flicking forked tongues in a spiraling duel. At
the top of the entangled serpents are clips to attach to the arm, with a small
bronze plate to protect them and the lower shoulders. The armlets are
certainly lighter and flashier than most mail, but provide adequate protection
at best.
